```suggestion
lemma legendre_eval_symm (n : ℕ) (x : ℝ) :
    eval x (Legendre n) = (-1) ^ n * eval (1 - x) (Legendre n) := by
```

```suggestion
    (x - y) ^ n = ∑ m ∈ range (n + 1), n.choose m • x ^ m * (- 1) ^ (n - m) * y ^ (n - m) := by
```

Please don't use lemmas from tactic implementations
```suggestion
  rw [sub_eq_add_neg, add_pow]
```

okk
It seems like that I need to pull sub pow first because Legendre.lean have used sub pow. Yes?

```suggestion
    (x - y) ^ n = ∑ m ∈ range (n + 1), (-1) ^ (m + n) * n.choose m • x ^ m * y ^ (n - m) := by
```
might be more canonical?
ok! I get it!
I don't really see the value in this lemma. You get this just by applying `sub_pow` and rewriting the terms in the obvious fashion. Can you inline it in your application?
emmmmm. I get it! It must be ok!
I worried that my proof is too long, so I separate it. ok. I'll inline it in my application.

```suggestion
  congr! 1 with m hm
  have : (-1 : R) ^ (n - m) = (-1) ^ (n + m) := by
    rw [mem_range] at hm
    simp [show n + m = n - m + 2 * m by omega, pow_add]
  rw [neg_pow, this]
  ring
```
thanks!
